          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-07-21 10:42:52" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>an instrument for weighing objects</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>balance scale</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>A balance scale may be described in some languages as ‘a tool for weighing’ or ‘an instrument for knowing how much something weighs.’ Ancient balance scales often consisted of a rod held by a cord in the middle and with pans attached to both ends. Weights could be placed in one pan, while the item to be weighed would be placed in the other.</Comments>
